<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/246: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-15T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 15,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>50. Your 56 April 13, 3 A.M.</p>
                        <p>Is Italian Government’s statement to be understood as meaning that
                            deliveries will not be made under contracts made either before or after
                            joint declaration made to Chinese Government May 5, 1919?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>